    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1926-05-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1926-05-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="233"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d233">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">638.5131/8</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The High Commissioner in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Russell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Port au Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-05-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 3, 1926</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received May 11.]</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 802</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to report that the Haitian
                    Government has addressed a note to the chargé d’affaires of the French
                    Government at Port-au-Prince, by the terms of which the Haitian Government
                    abrogates, on the 27th of July next, the Franco-Haitian Commercial Convention of
                        1907.<note n="9" xml:id="d233fn9">Signed Jan. 30, 1907; <hi rend="italic"
                            >British and Foreign State Papers</hi>, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >c</hi>, p. 911.</note>
                </p>
                <p>A copy and translation of the note, together with two other notes bearing
                    thereon, are transmitted herewith for the Department’s information.<note n="10"
                        xml:id="d233fn10">None printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John H. Russell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
